      "content": "It's not uncommon for asthma symptoms to worsen with age, but it's always best to consult a doctor to rule out any potential complications. Taking a higher dose of your salbutamol inhaler may not be the solution, as it could indicate increased inflammation or other underlying issues. I recommend scheduling an appointment with your doctor to discuss your symptoms and determine the best course of action. They can assess your condition and adjust your treatment plan accordingly.",
      "source": "target",
